- Ferroptosis modulation affecting pulmonary fibrosis
- MRC-5 cells as a standard model for lung fibrosis research
- Antioxidants & Redox Signaling as the appropriate publication venue

However, the exact title cannot be determined from the available search results within the constraints of the maximum search limit.

## Conclusion

Based on the extensive research conducted, the following has been established:

- **Journal**: Antioxidants & Redox Signaling (official journal of the Society for Redox Biology and Medicine)
- **Protein**: System xc- (SLC7A11/SLC3A2 heteromeric amino acid transporter)
- **Inhibitor Drug**: Sulfasalazine (anti-cancer/antibacterial drug)
- **Amino Acid Transported**: Cystine (imported), Glutamate (exported)
- **Tripeptide Produced**: Glutathione
- **Pathway**: Glutathione/redox pathway affecting ferroptosis
- **Disease**: Pulmonary fibrosis (lung scarring)
- **Cell Line**: MRC-5 (human fetal lung fibroblasts)

